Package org.apache.axis2.jaxws.server.dispatcher

Interface Summary
EndpointDispatcher The EndpointDispatcher is an abstraction for the object that will be doing the invocation of an endpoints target Java object.
 

Class Summary
JavaBeanDispatcher The JavaBeanDispatcher is used to manage creating an instance of a JAX-WS service implementation bean and dispatching the inbound request to that instance.
JavaDispatcher JavaDispatcher is an abstract class that can be extended to implement an EndpointDispatcher to a Java object.
ProviderDispatcher The ProviderDispatcher is used to invoke instances of a target endpoint that implement the Provider interface.
